# pcli — HPE ProLiant unified CLI

A unified command-line tool for managing HPE ProLiant servers across direct iLO access and the HPE GreenLake cloud.

## Installation

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd pcli
pip install -e ".[all]"
```

## Usage

```
pcli ilo <command>    # Direct iLO Redfish management
pcli com <command>    # HPE GreenLake / Compute Ops Management
```

### iLO commands

```bash
pcli ilo init                              # Create starter hosts.yml config
pcli ilo show fleet                        # Firmware summary across all hosts
pcli ilo show ilo                          # iLO firmware versions
pcli ilo show network                      # NIC firmware versions
pcli ilo show storage                      # Storage controllers + drives
pcli ilo show bios                         # BIOS/System ROM versions
pcli ilo show cpu                          # CPU models + microcode
pcli ilo show memory                       # DIMM details
pcli ilo show full                         # Full firmware inventory
pcli ilo upgrade --host myilo              # Auto-upgrade all firmware from HPE SDR
pcli ilo upgrade --host myilo --dry-run    # Preview without changes
pcli ilo upgrade --host myilo --reboot     # Upgrade and reboot
```

### COM commands

```bash
pcli com login                             # Login to HPE GreenLake (Okta or API client)
pcli com logout                            # Remove cached credentials
pcli com get devices                       # List all devices in workspace
pcli com get devices --type COMPUTE        # Filter by type
pcli com get workspaces                    # List workspaces
pcli com use workspace <name>              # Switch active workspace
```

## Config files

- iLO hosts: `~/.config/pcli/ilo/hosts.yml`
- COM credentials: `~/.config/pcli/com/credentials.yml`
- COM token cache: `~/.config/pcli/com/token.json`
